description: Tens of thousands of people gathered in the Israeli city on Saturday night, determined to believe in the release of the last hostages held in Gaza. Many are also deeply concerned about the rise of pro-Palestinian protests across Europe.

Returning to Spain after generations of exile
description: The country is experiencing a sharp rise in population, driven by a wave of 'grandchildren' settling in the land of their ancestors who fled Francoist Spain, a place to which they feel attached, despite never having lived there.

headline: US federal agent shoots Chicago motorist as protests spread, while a judge blocks troops to Portland
description: Illinois Governor JB Pritzker announced the Trump administration's plans to federalize 300 members of the Illinois National Guard, calling the decision 'absolutely outrageous and un-American.' Also on Saturday, US District Judge Karin Immergut blocked Trump's bid to deploy troops into Portland.

headline: Madagascar's President Andry Rajoelina loses the battle for the streets
description: The Malagasy president failed on Saturday to rally his supporters to demonstrate their backing after 10 days of protests led by Generation Z.

headline: The West Bank village of Palestine's forgotten Americans
description: In the occupied West Bank, 85% of Turmus Ayya's population are American-Palestinian citizens. Every summer, these dual nationals return to visit their families and maintain ties with their homeland. They find that their American passports offer no immunity from persecution by the army and settlers in this territory, where illegal Israeli settlements are rapidly expanding.

Le Monde enters Gaza City, an ocean of ruins emptied of its people
description: Le Monde's Jerusalem correspondent entered the Palestinian urban area for a few hours on Friday, October 3, under escort from the Israel Defense Forces (IDF). The territory, largely destroyed by airstrikes and bulldozers, was utterly deserted, with nearly all residents having fled south within the enclave.

headline: Trump turns the government shutdown into a political weapon
description: The American president considers the partial halt of government operations − triggered by budget disagreements between Republicans and Democrats − an opportunity to further dismantle the federal state and win a PR war against his opponents.

headline: Why foreigners love France but struggle with the French
description: While France captivates with its culture and lifestyle, the French, frequently caricatured as arrogant and impolite, often have a poor reputation. This ambivalence raises questions about the roots of anti-French sentiment abroad.
